To the know it all Marine,<br>
     So, let me get this straight!  You are perfectly willing to accept a view of the Vietnam Vet like Oliver Stone is willing to portray?  In case you are not familiar with his movie Platoon, it portrays the members of a combat line unit as drug users, killers and rapists.  Did you enjoy<br>
the scene in the movie where the soldiers raped little girls?  How about Brian De Palma's Casualties of War?  Do you agree that GI's kidnapped girls on a regular basis, and then raped and killed them?  Have you seen enough 1970's cop shows, like Hawaii 5-0, where it seems almost every week, a paranoid, insane Vietnam Vet killed someone or took hostages? It case you don't realize this you mental giant, 2,594,000 decent young American men and women served in Vietnam.  They are now defused into a American population that is now about 240 million.  That leaves a lot of people that were not in Vietnam, not to mention that Nam vets are only 9.7% of the postwar Baby Boomer male population.  Also, since then a whole new generation has been born with little or no memory of the war.  These people get their perceptions and images from what the media presents on TV and in the movies.  I am a school teacher and a damn good one, I am seeing children that view and understand Vietnam from the twisted media images.  Not every child is fortunate enough to have a brave, dedicated man who was a decorated Nam-Vet as a father to put them straight about what happen over there for real, instead of Platoon, Casualties of War or those horrible CBS news documentaries on Vietnam Vets.  That's another one, do you remember Dan Rathers's documentary in the 80's on those crazy Nam Vets in Washington State?  They show guys living like animals and howling at the moon.  These guys were confessing to comitting genocide and creulty on civilans that makes Hitler look like Mother Teresa (no disrespect to her), especially since these men wher never in Vietnam or these acts where never proved.  Do you know any vets that howl at the moon.  I don't, and I know many Nam Vets through the veterans post!  Let me tell you something Mr. Know it all, that documentary is now shown in many schools across America to instruct children on how the war messed up men big time.  I would never show that movie, because I know Nam Vets are not like that.  Do you want your children or grandchildren to grow up thinking that's the way Vietnam was.  The reason many Americans believe this is true is because they don't know any better and believe what they see on TV.  No on, especially me disputes that the war was all wrong.  It made me sad when I saw the memorial!  Our allies were useless, and so was the terrible war.  What I hate is the indifferernt Vets like you that allow Americans to accept Platoon as the end all-be all on Vietnam.  I am just glad that some vets are willing to speak to our children and students and tell the truth, so they don't see or read what some liberal, probabely anti-war writer or Hollywood producer thinks Vietnam was like.  97% of all Vietnam era soldiers were honorably discharged.  How many Americans know this?  How about the million acts of kindness that were shown to the Vietnamese people.  Almost every documentary and history textbook on Vietnam dwells on My Lai and not the acts of kindness.  How about the countless college students,<br>
that study the genocides we committed on innocent rice farmers with no study on how we helped instead of hurt.  My ax is to try to erase these useless perceptions on Nam vets that are untrue.  I care about how Nam Vets are perceived!  America doesn't view World War II vets with the same suspicion that they lavish on Vietnam.  As a teacher, writer, and historian, I am trying to aid in a positive perception on the Vietnam Vets that will be the facts for another up and coming generation.  I guess some vets like you don't care, unless you agree with the media and believe the &quot;Platoon&quot; image is true.  Every other Marine, I talked to did a upstanding job and agree with me, so what is your problem?  
